शिवमंदिर मे चार-पाँच गंजेडी
रोज गाँजा पीते थे,
पिछले कई साल से जब भी वो
गाँजा पीते थे तब "बम भोले" का
जयकारा करते थे
चिल्लम की हर फुँक के साथ,
.
.
एक दिन खुद शिव जी उनके इस भक्ति
माध्यम से
प्रसन्न हो गये,
.
वो एक साधारण मनुष्य के रूप मे उन गंजेडीयो के
पास आ कर बैठ गये,
.
गंजेडीयो ने चिल्लम बनाना शुरू किया
तो एक गंजेडी ने शिव जी को
गाँजा आफर किया,
.
प्रायः गंजेडीयो मे मेहमानवाजी
बडे उच्च स्तर की होती है,
इसलिए गंजेडीयो ने पहला चिल्लम
भोलेनाथ को ही दिया,
.
एक फुँक मे ही शिव जी ने पुरा चिल्लम खाली कर
दिया ,
गंजेडीयो को लग गया कि ये कोई उच्च
कोटी का पीने वाला है,
फिर
उन्होने दुसरा चिल्लम बनाया
और फिर पहला मौका भोलेनाथ को दिया
,
शिव जी ने फिर एक फुँक मे ही पुरा चिल्लम खाली
कर दिया,
.
हर फुँक के बाद एक गंजेडी, भोलेनाथ से पुछता रहा :
"नशा आया" ?
.
जवाब मे शिव जी केवल मुस्कुरा के 'ना' मे सर हिला
देते,
.
ऐसे कर के जब पाँच चिल्लम खाली हो गये तो
गंजेडी आखिरी चिल्लम भरने लगे तभी उनमे से एक
गंजेडी ने पुछा : " क्यों अभी भी नशा नही हुआ ? "
.
तब शिव जी ने कहा : "जानते हो मै कौन हुँ ?"
.
गंजेडी : "कौन हो भाऊ ? "
.
शिव जी : " मै इस ससांर का सहाँरक, सभी भुत, प्रेत,
यक्ष, असुर, गंधर्व का स्वामी, ब्रम्हाड का
आदिवासी, हिमालय का निवासी हुँ,
आदि
अंत - प्रारंभ, नाश और नशा सब की सीमा
मुझसे
प्रारंभ होती है और मुझ पर ही खत्म, शकंर नाम है मेरा,
जिसको तुम लोग रोज याद करते हो "
.
.
.
.
गंजेडी जोर से चिल्लाया : " अब इसको और
चिल्लम
मत देना बे , गाँजा चढ गया इसको

The shutters of 35 out of 40 dams in Kerala have been opened for the first time in the history.

We would request all the students of NIT Durgapur to contribute to this noble cause. It’s our duty to help the people in need.

27/09/2018, 00:58 - Manisha @ NIT Dgp Civil: Stuck at a level of your gaming conquest ?! Take a break and channel your humor through memes.

So, this Aavishkar get your meme game on and let your humor win the game for you. Send in your originally created memes on any game of choice for the pre-Aavishkar event *MEME-DINGER* via: 
Messenger - *https://www.facebook.com/aavishkar.nitd/*
or
E-mail - *submissions@avskr.in*

*RULES:*
Memes can be of any type on any game that you like. Also it must be an original creation (OC). 

*SCORING:*
React 2 points, Comment 3 points, Share 5 points.
Note that in order to make an entry, or react to an entry, *you must like the Aavishkar page*. 
In case of a tie, the post with *maximum shares* will be declared the winner.
Comments or reacts from the person posting the meme will not be considered for scoring.

10/03/2019, 11:39 - Piyush @ NIT Dgp Civil: "वो पैगाम ही क्या जो किसी के नाम ना हो।
औऱ वो दिन ही क्या जिसकी कोई गुलजार-ए-शाम ना हो!!"

ऐसी ही एक शाम को गुलजार करने के लिए *हिंदी छात्र संघ 'दर्पण'* लेकर आ रहा है कार्यक्रम- *"झंकार"*, जिसका मुख्य उद्देश्य मनोरंजन के साथ-साथ संगीत-गायन,नृत्य औऱ काव्यगत प्रतिभा वाले विद्यार्थियों को उजागर करने के लिए मंच प्रदान करना है। ताकि ऐसे प्रतिभाशाली विद्यार्थियों को पहचान एवं प्रोत्साहन मिल सके।

इस कार्यक्रम के मुख्य रुप से तीन भाग हैं-
1. तरंग (Singing comptition)
2. नटराजन (Dancing comptition)
3. ओपन माइक (Open mic)

इन कार्यक्रम के विजेताओं को तत्काल *नकद ईनाम* (Instant cash prizes upto ₹3500 for each event)औऱ प्रोत्साहन के लिए प्रमाण-पत्र भी प्रदान किया जायेगा।

इन सभी कार्यक्रमों के साथ साथ मुख्य आकर्षण का केंद्र दुर्गापुर की *'सांस्कृतिक संगीत मंडली'* का प्रस्तुतिकरण(performance) होगा जो आपके हृदय को उत्साह एवं हर्ष से भर देगा। कार्यक्रम के दौरान जलपान की भी व्यवस्था रहेगी।
 
तो आइए इस मनोरंजक शाम का हिस्सा बनिए औऱ कार्यक्रम में प्रतिभाग करके नकद ईनाम जीतने का मौका पाइये।

ऊपर दिये गये कार्यक्रमों में प्रतिभाग(perform) करने के लिए नीचे दिये गये 'गूगल फार्म'(Google form) को भरकर जल्द से जल्द रजिस्टर करें-

https://goo.gl/forms/YIY6Oz8IY9n8V53G3

Venue- SAC
Time- 5:30pm onwards

कार्यक्रम में प्रतिभाग(perform) करने के लिए नीचे दिये गये 'गूगल फार्म'(Google form) को भरकर जल्द से जल्द रजिस्टर करें-

https://goo.gl/forms/YIY6Oz8IY9n8V53G3

Date- March 12th,2019
Venue- SAC
Time- 5:30pm onwards
11/03/2019, 12:00 - Madhav Mishra @ NIT Dgp | Civil: <Media omitted>
11/03/2019, 12:00 - Madhav Mishra @ NIT Dgp | Civil: हज़ारों ख्वाइशें ऐसी की हर ख्वाहिश पे दम निकले |
बहुत निकले मेरे अरमां मगर फिर भी कम निकले || 

हिंदी  छात्र संघ 'दर्पण' देता है  आपकी  हर ख्वाहिश ,हर अरमां को महफ़िल -ए- शाम "झंकार" में बयां करने का एक सुनहरा अवसर | 
ये  आपकी भावनाओं और प्रतिभाओं को लोगों के सामने प्रदर्शित करने का मौका प्रदान करता है जिससे की आप अपने अंदर छुपी प्रतिभा को तहे दिल से  बिना किसी झिझक के  लोगों के सामने व्यक्त कर सकें । इसमें आप Stand up Comedy ,कविता पाठ, Story Telling,Dialogue Delivery ,शायरी  के  माध्यम से अपनी प्रतिभा का प्रदर्शन कर सकते हैं |
तो आइये और अपने समय का सदुपयोग करते हुए इन लम्हों को अपने लिए महत्वपूर्ण बनाइये एवं दुसरो के दिलो पे अपनी छाप छोड़ जाइये ...

With events ranging from singing competition ‘Tarang’, dancing competition ‘Natrajan’ to open MIC competition, the whole stage is set for you to perform and perceive an evening worth remembering. Instant cash prizes for winners worth Rs 10,000.
TARANG: The participants can sing any genre of song in either Hindi or Bengali. The performance can be solo/duet/group (Background music will be provided if the song is informed beforehand).
NATRAJAN: The participants can perform any form of dance in solo/duet/ group.  
OPEN MIC: The participants shall have the liberty to present anything of her/his choice. The presentation maybe a poetry/ stand up comedy/ speech/ mimicry etc.
You can register yourself for the event through the link given below.
https://goo.gl/forms/YIY6Oz8IY9n8V53G3
 On spot registration will also be available at the venue.
Hoping to see a grand response of students at the event.

08/05/2019, 16:13 - Abishek @ NIT Dgp | Civil: To every student of NIT Durgapur.

Freedom is everything a person wants in life,but we should never take this as granted. 

The whole NIT Durgapur campus started celebrating two months back when the authority removed the hostel in times. *But it was based on a CONDITION that any student must NOT go into professor's residential area after 10 PM.*

It has been brought to our notice that-
1) *Few students (Boys & Girls) are not following this and are creating obscene in professor's residential area.*

2) *After having night-out in Ovals Ground, students are leaving the water bottles, Beer Bottles, Wrappers and other garbages on the ground making it awfully dirty.*

If such things go on happening,the authority is  going to revert back implementing the previous in-time for Students very soon.

It is a request and suggestions from Batch of 2015-19 to juniors that do not take your freedom as granted. Know your limitations and make sure that you provide your juniors a better NIT Durgapur.

-Batch 2015-19

26/07/2019, 18:50 - Subhash Dixit: It's time to shape the student's body of *NIT Durgapur, the Gymkhana.*

By shaping, we mean effective conveyance of your voice to the  authorities. The election is the mechanism of putting forward the best men to express the voice of the entire NIT Durgapur students community.

Being a final year student, I have seen the problems faced by the students in day-to-day life. I intend to solve them. I wish to stand by you in your need. By coming forward as the *Vice-Presidential candidate*, I want to impart a meaningful and productive campus life to all the students of NIT Durgapur.

There are problems in this college which needs to be solved urgently, and choosing the right candidate will get that done.

26/07/2019, 19:36 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: <Media omitted>
26/07/2019, 20:20 - Arpan Jaiswal @ NIT Dgp | Civil: *The Students' Gymkhana* is the students' administrative body of NIT Durgapur. The Gymkhana acts as a bridge between students and college administration to address the issues faced by students at different fronts in college life. 
The Gymkhana also organizes *_RECSTACY_*, the annual cultural fest of our college.
*What role do you play?*
A Gymkhana is not a club, _it’s a Student body_, formed and elected with _cooperation and assistance of our students_. The body puts forth real-time problems before the college authorities to which they wouldn’t pay attention to otherwise.  Hence, it’s very crucial that you *choose your candidate, your Gymkhana wisely*. 
*How to get involved?*
_First things first._
You should first know about the *different positions in the Gymkhana*, *the candidates* contesting for them, *the team working along with the candidates* and the _*AGENDAS*_ proposed by them.
You should align your issues with the agendas that address your problems and finally, choose your candidate accordingly.
*What next?*
Elections are around the corner.  *Get ready to experience your first ever Gymkhana elections* and keep yourself boosted for further updates.

*PIYUSH BHATIA*
_Presidential Candidate_
(Students’ Gymkhana)

 *MANISH AWASTHI* 
 _General Secretary_ _Candidate_

10/08/2019, 19:37 - Amandeep @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Sir, 
I am writing you this letter on behalf of every student of the civil engineering department, 3rd year.  I wanted to share with you,  what mental  pressure every student of our year is facing. 
 Firstly,  everyone of us have worked hard day and night and cleared the JEE MAINS exam to reach this place,  moreover a government institution which everyone believed to be very good.  But the quality of education we are getting here is not up to its mark. Here teachers having one background are teaching subjects of another background,  making an easy and interesting subject, a boring and a difficult one.  There are only few of the teachers  in the department,  we believe to be very good. Not a single student misses their classes.  
    Secondly, the number of classes we are having every week is very high. Specially on fridays, we are having our surveying sessional class under the hot sun from 9-15am to 12-15pm and from 1-15pm to 5-10pm we are forced to attend the soil mechanics classes for four long hours because the guest lecturer could come for only one day. It is very difficult to concentrate on a particular subject for four long hours after getting tired under the hot sun. As a result,  just for the sake of attendance every student is wasting its valuable four hours. I would like to bring your attention on another instance. We are being forced to give tests in the evening beyond the class hours,  making our schedule more hectic. 
  Sir,  I would also like to bring before you how teachers are also mentally harass students. One of the professor kept on forcing one student to tell him the reason for being absent since the beginning of this semester, despite the student being saying that he is having some family problems,  which he could not share in front of the entire class.  He was very shy.  The same professor promised another student that he will not let him pass until he is present in this department as a professor. Another professor promised us in the last semester that there is no need of attending his classes.  He clearly stated that he will be making everybody's attendance equal to 75% and he will be passing every student.  Even if a student is failing to score a passing mark,  he will be passing him with a 'P' grade.  But this did not happen. Many students were given backlog. The same professor last week,  boring and one of the student to stand in the hot sun during the sessional class and did not let him use a umbrella.  The student politely told him that he is having some skin infection and doctor had clearly instructed him not to stand under the sun. The way the teacher shouted at him was very bad and insulting. 
   We believe that everyone after working so hard,  deserve a valuable job,  but the placements of our department were the worst in this year. Many of the TPRs approached the TEST regarding improving the conditions of our department,  but the TPSW did not responded positively,  stating that he is too busy and cannot help us in this matter.  Also,  the last option which we are left is appearing for the GATE examination, secure a good rank and get a job for oneself.  But this preparation also requires a lot of time and patience.  After attending so many worthless classes,  having a mental pressure,  writing bundles and bundles of assignments,  we are left with no time to prepare for ourselves. The entire frustration which we are having,  we outburst it in front of our parents,  which I believe is very wrong. 
Nearly 40 students from the CS, IT, ECE department have got internship,  but we the civil engineering student are not getting any opportunity to bag an internship or prepare for the GATE examination. As a result,  we can see our future completely dark. Since,  we are working hard,  we also deserve a job in our field. We are no less than the IT sector students.  We have the maximum of the core subjects.  It is not easy as that of the IT sector students to learn a particular programming language and master.  All our core subjects are no where interrelated.
 So, I would like to conclude that something must be done at the earliest to improve the placements of our department,  if the classes cannot be reduced or we should be given time to prepare for GATE by reducing the number of classes. We will be highly obliged if the quality of education can be improved.There are no teachers to whom we can approach beyond the class hours to clear our doubts of the GATE.

10/08/2019, 21:14 - Aneek Biswas @ NIT Dgp Civil: Sir,
This letter is being written on behalf of the entire Civil Engineering batch, currently in fifth semester, to express our grievances regarding the functionalities and other aspects of our department. 
•	The most important aspect of any department, i.e. placement is disastrous in our department. Recent placement statistics reveal that Civil Engineering saw just 39% placement, out of which just 23% were placed in core companies – a percentage that may be outshone by any NIT in our country. There is no particular initiative taken by the TPSW to bring in new companies, neither the TPRs are given any specific power in inviting new companies to the college. The students who are interested in coding/web-development are majorly ignored, only two companies have been opened for Civil Engineering till now, out of which one of our students have made it to top five among 250 participating students. Thus, we have the talent, but no opportunity to harness it. 
•	We are having 35 hours of class in the available 40 hours per week, a figure that is enough to justify the pressure that is being handled by the students. Not only this, there are faculties that are forcing students to appear for practical examinations in evening from 6 pm or in holidays. Sir, given the multitude of the syllabus that we have to study not only for the semesters, but also for GATE, such kind of schedule is completely hindering the students from doing so. 
•	Serious issues like health problems, family issues and personal problems are neglected by the teachers as ‘lack of discipline and focus’ and any student who miss the classes due to abovementioned reasons are refused attendance even after producing relevant documents. We have numerous incidents, where students were roughly forced to attend the class or leave, despite having unavoidable reasons. 
•	Most of our professors are much senior, whose voice is inaudible to most of the class. Despite having facilities for microphone and speakers available, they refuse to use them and the students simply have to sit in class for the sake of attendance. 
•	The laboratories are in the worst condition. There is no proper lighting, no ventilation inside the lab, and there aren’t sufficient instruments that can be demonstrated and made available to each and every student. The excuse of ‘lack of funds’ simply baffles us, considering we belong to an institute of national importance.

Hence, we propose the following changes and rectifications that can be done:

•	Improvement of Placement: More power should be given to TPRs of respective departments, rather than two associate deans belonging to two departments. EQUAL DISTRIBUTION OF ATTENTION REGARDING TRAINING AND PLACEMENT TO ALL DEPARTMENTS should be enforced immediately and properly. The training and placement representative professor of the department must take incentives to invite more core companies and provide opportunity to the students they deserve.
•	Reduction in class-hours: Class hours is directly related to number of credits, and hence should be taken accordingly. Attending classes on holidays and in evening is something that is illogical and irrational.
•	Special attention to medical/personal issues: Enforcing physically/mentally ill people to attend class is something that violates the general values. Professors are bound to pay attention to them and consider their attendance.
•	Improvement of Laboratories: Civil Engineering is a department that is solely based on field experience; hence it can be said that we are the ones who require the highest facility of labs and facilities to provide us with genuine field experience. Improvement of lab facilities, inception of advanced machines and instruments and implementing more educated lab assistants should be done immediately.

Sir, hence we hope that you understand that we are not in a positive position altogether. We care not only for us but also for the future batches that will face the same injustice if not addressed by the higher authority. After all, we all want to shine in our respective areas and ultimately make our department and our college proud in near future. Hence, we would be ever-thankful to you if you listen to our pleas and take some step to ensure a better future for one of the oldest departments of our college.
Yours sincerely,
Civil Engineering Department
(Currently in third year)

Today a meeting was scheduled with the SDO Durgapur, who respectfully ensured his co-operation, although he also made sure only 3 student delegates for the meeting. Had it been earlier ,it was planned to show a full student support on 13/08/2019.
Next step was lodging  an FIR against the veg mess protesters but the police were reluctant to do so as a result of which we had to meet the mayor regarding this matter. On his intervention, after so many efforts, *the police finally lodged the FIR.*
The crux is , *tomorrow the students will be attending their regular classes*, however if the circumstances arise the Gymkhana will be prompt to act accordingly and the students will be informed regarding the same.
As Classes were suspended today the attendance for the same has  been considered and a copy of the mail by Dean Student & Welfare has been forwarded to all the faculty  members whose copy is attached herewith.
 
We thank all the students for showing the support and expect the same in future.

*Students Gymkhana.*

1. All the classes will be suspended until 31st March.

2. The local students need to vacate the hostels until 31st March. All international students can reside in their hostels, with due permissions from their hostel warden.

-Student's Gymkhana, NIT Durgapur

24/03/2020, 12:32 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Students of 6th Sem batch of CE,

In view of the prevailing critical situation in our country & elsewhere, please utilise your time in studying / practising of course contents in your home till normalcy returns. 

In this regard I am forwarding the information about an online course material (as mentioned above) that you should start following immediately so that we can speed up the course coverage in class once the Institute reopens. Also please refer to the text books suggested in the beginning of the course, whenever possible. We will finish discussing the small remaining part of the Water Supply portion of the syllabus when classes restart.  As we have already discussed the basics of design of water treatment units, I hope you will be able to follow these study materials about the Wastewater Engineering (effectively the 2nd half of the syllabus) without much difficulty. In spite of this, if you need some clarifications about the subject topics, please feel free to contact me by mail. However, I hope you will find the web course material suggested below useful & easy to follow.

Please go to the course material as per the following through NITD website :

28/03/2020, 12:57 - Aneek Biswas @ NIT Dgp Civil: People who have got internships via the interview procedure,
As you understand, we are right now in a situation where things are very uncertain. We dont know when will this outbreak end and what turn the pandemic will take next. 
There are a lot of probabilities as to how to conduct the internships and when to conduct. Nothing can be said with assurity until and unless the college issues the modified academic calender.
Once they issue it, we can know what is the timeline and then plan accordingly with the companies. 

So stay patient and dont panic. Let's hope for the best.

05/04/2020, 19:56 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Students of 6th Sem batch of CE, 

Hope you are aware from the recent notifications available in NITD website that summer vacation has been declared in the Institute from 04.04.2020 & it is scheduled to continue upto 31.05.2020. Whatever be the actual date of classes to restart, it appears that very small period will be left for classes after the vacation before semester examinations start. Thus you should try to cover the course content of the theory papers (in this case CEC603) as much as possible within the vacation period. As we have started communicating since 24.03.2020 through our initial set of comprehensive study material available from NPTEL, I hope you will be able to cover the course content without much trouble.

I am now enclosing a pdf version of a standard textbook on wastewater engineering by an Indian author (S. K. Garg). You may follow similar text materials, if already available with you. This may appear to be a more conventional form of study material that contains worked out problems as well. I am also enclosing an instruction sheet for following this text book (presently upto Chapter 8 as treatment of wastewater will start from Chapter 9 and similar instructions will follow for the same in my later mails). The file size being more than 150mb, it is to be downloaded through Google drive that, I think, is known to all of you.

However, I suggest this material to be considered in association with the series of video lectures of NPTEL suggested earlier for better understanding of the subject. Together, they may be considered comprehensive study material for CEC603.



                   -  *S.B sir*

06/04/2020, 10:40 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Students of VI sem CE batch,

I am once again sending you the attachment as mentioned above,

The problem of file sharing with multiple recipients  through google drive is a technical one. Yesterday I got a choice of setting as follows:
(i) To 2 users
(ii) To everybody in NIT Durgapur.

13/05/2020, 12:56 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Sir,

 

Greetings on behalf of EEEs Academy.

 

TO SUPPORT the students for their summer Training/ learning, which has been affected due to lockdown/COVID 19, We have initiated an ONLINE practical learning program for the Civil Engineering students. Request you to kindly forward the mail to the FINAL YEAR students of CIVIL Engineering of your college for their benefit.

 

We would be glad to have maximum number of participants/ students from your Organization/ College. General details of the Training/Workshop are as below:

 

Online Training/Workshop on Structural Design Requirements and Structural Design using STAAD Pro covering IS456, IS1893 and IS13920

 

Key Topics :

 

·         Applicable Indian Standards for Structural Design of RCC buildings

·         Design Loads, Concrete Durability 

·         Concept of Service Life of Building 

·         Structural Analysis and Design Concept w.r.t Indian Standards

·         Concept of Ductility

·         Reinforcement Detailing Concepts

·         CASE STUDY : Structural Design of an Actual Project using STAAD Pro.

 

Key Faculty : - Mr. Aman Deep (expert of several technical committees of BIS and Faculty of many Trainings/Workshops)

                           Mr. Manik Chatterjee (expert of Earthquake Committee of BIS, Consultant and Researcher)                              

 

Participant Profile: BE/ B Tech- Civil Engineering (3rd and 4th year) students, M.Tech (Structure) Students, fresh working professionals

 

Training/Workshop Duration and Venue: The Training/Workshop will be 2 months long comprehensive having 3 weekly online sessions of around 90min as well as doubt clearing sessions and weekly assignments.

Training/Workshop will be on Zoom online Training.

 

How to apply:

 

*  Revert to my email (or mail to: eeeacademyenquiry@gmail.com) for registration.

The training would be provided at a nominal fee of Rs5000/- only per student. For working professionals, the Fee is Rs6000/- only. For registrations before 24th May, early bird Discount of 10% is also available on the Fee.

For any enquiry/ suggestion, we may be contact our mobile call or on WhatsApp at 8077816094/  8860062494

Expected outcome of the Workshop/Training

·         Participants would be confident about the  Provision/ requirements of Indian Standards.

·         Clarity about the Structural Design Concepts, planning and durable Construction.

·         Exposure and understanding about the Earthquake forces and Structural Design requirements.

·         Understanding and ability of the candidate would be developed for Reinforcement detailing 

·         Misc. technical aspects would be clarified so as to have better and faster output of Engineer

 

Looking forward for your support for spreading the communication and confirmation of participants from your esteemed Organization/College.

 

Regards

Anshul Sharma

Programme Coordinator

Mob : 8860062494

EEEs Academy

408, SG Alpha Tower-1,

Sector 9, Vasundhara, Ghaziabad-201012

www.ccepl.co.in

Many students belonging to this category are unable to prepare smartly for the *Core Companies* mainly because of absence of proper guidance and resources such as company wise sorted interview questions and solutions etc. that CS/IT students get easily.

We therefore *aim to create an organised platform for all such students aiming for Core Profiled Jobs* to give them easy access to details related to job profiles, questions asked, interview rounds and how to prepare for them.

*The Gymkhana, NIT Durgapur* hopes everyone is doing well, during these times of utmost crisis.
The pandemic has created an unbeatable whirlpool which has made it difficult for normalcy to return. As students, we are the ones facing a lot of challenges be it the approach being implemented to run parallel with the syllabus or acquiring skills for assisting our career. 

Meanwhile, many institutions have called off the even-semesters and many have come up with different methodologies for the evaluation of the respective semester. It's high time that even our institution takes some concrete decision.

So, *we are inviting you to give a robust solution for an alternative to our semester exams. Even if it's the cancellation of the same please put in your response*.

  2.  Join in a team of 10 students according to your roll number in ascending order.

18/07/2020, 14:47 - Aneek Biswas @ NIT Dgp Civil: Hello,
Hope you all are safe and healthy.

Please carefully read this at your own interest.

I guess we need not tell you seperately the grave condition we are in. With the country still in hopeless condition as the COVID-19 cases are rising exponentially on a daily basis, education sector is one of the worst hit sector. With transportation facilities remaining uncertain and mostly marked unsafe, students are stranded in various parts of the country in their own hometown. Undoudtedly this has affected the placement scenario drastically. Since we civil engineers are mostly engaged in site-based jobs, the situation has been more harsh for us. Even the two organisations that previously came for recruiting interns are now uncertain regarding the internship scenario. We are planning on initiating the placement session for our academic year as soon as possible but we hope you understand that the placement session this year won't be the same as in previous years.

Hence we decided to come up with some suggestions that may help you to stay upbeat about the placement scenario. The silver lining in this circumstance is that, IT companies or Finance based companies, although affected, but still since they have provision for work from home, they are on a slightly less vulnerable zone as compared to the core sectors. The first wave of companies that are about to arrive in the college are mostly IT companies anong which some may be open to all, and then the second wave will comprise of open to all companies mostly based on business analytics/finance. These are very rough estimations, but all over the country, almost similar trends are followed. We have already started contacting them and they can conduct placement sessions anytime after mid August. 
So those who are willing to appear in these sessions can do the following things to improve your chances:
- Learn a programming language : Python is the most commonly used language nowadays and has varieties of applications. You can learn a course from Coursera or Udemy. 
- Start practising for the aptitude based questions from indiabix.com. They would be an essential for every single online test, more for the analytics companies.
- Learn a frontend interface like HTML, PHP, CSS. They are easier than Python and web development is a hot-cake in todays market. 
- Last but not the least, start mailing professors across the country in IITs and NITs for scope of a virtual internship. This would surely add up to your experience.

This was all we had to say. We are not trying to divert you from joining the core companies, but this is just a heads up, as situation is different as in other times. We want all of us to not get devastated, but rather stay uplifted and hopeful that this may also pass. The first phase will begin anytime in next month so be prepared. And mean while we are always working to ensure the core companies remain in touch with the placement cell despite of this pandemic.

Stay safe,
TPRs of Civil Engineering Department

21/07/2020, 01:07 - Aneek Biswas @ NIT Dgp Civil: Dear Students,


The new placement Season (2020-21) is expected to be in a different format, given the pandemic situation in the country arising out of rapidly spreading Covid 19. Different institutes and universities as well as the Govt. of India are keeping a strict vigil on the ever changing situation and thinking of evaluating the different possible options.


The placement cell at NIT Durgapur is also in close touch with all the organizations. Our honorable Director Sir has also conveyed a message to all the companies who come for recruitment to co-operate and promised full cooperation from us. 

We are thinking and considering the alternative to kick start the full time placement and internship recruitment process for the 2020 -2021season in online/ virtual  mode along with the traditional modes. 


However, though not ideal, this option is feasible only for those who have access to reliable internet connection and a digital access device. 


Presently, we are just trying to collect reliable data about your accessibility. 

We request you to provide the true information on honour code declaration, and fill up both. The TPRs are requested to collate the data for their department and send the information to the placement cell.


1.The Table given below 


2.	Fill up the Google form 

https://forms.gle/oVF6QKiyUJRdebs37



This is required to reach the placement cell by 27th July 2020.  Basis this survey results we can proceed to fix dates with the companies.


The final decision will be taken later on collection of more information and assessment of the situation.


Name:						

Roll Number:

Dept.

Course						

Year

Semester

Question Type 1 for Yes and 0 for No


1. Do you have access to a PC/Laptop?	

2. Do you have access to a Smartphone?	

3. Do you have access to stable internet?	

4. Do you have a 4G connection?	

5. Do you have a 3G connection?

6. Do you agree to sit for online/virtual mode of internship recruitment process?

7. Do you agree to sit for online/virtual mode of full time placement recruitment process

*It has been brought to our notice that some students are organizing mass mail campaigns to ask the administration regarding fee reductions for the upcoming semester.*

*The Student's Gymkhana has already held it's executive council meeting along with class representatives  and are looking into the matter. We would be reaching out to administration and conveying all your grievances and opinions. All we require from you is patience and constant cooperation from your end. We would soon be collecting your opinions via online methods.*

*The Gymkhana works for the Student's welfare and will continue to do that. We request you to not take any rash and irresponsible steps which might undermine our efforts. Moreover the responsibility of Student's irresponsible acts won't be taken up by the Student's Gymkhana.*

*FYI : NIT Durgapur will be joining an All India Association termed as PAN NIT Council to uphold the Student's voices to the Ministry of Human Resource and Development (MHRD) and also to have a Nationwide collective approach to the student crisis in view of the Pandemic. More information  will be made available in due process.*

*Reach out to us if you have any doubts regarding the above via the department representatives.*

*Best Regards,*

*Student's Gymkhana*

*IIT Bombay, BITS Pilani, NIT Rourkela* among many have collaborated with us to help prepare their students for placements.

The session would be conducted by *Ex-Placement Head of IIT Bombay*, Ex-Placement team member of IIT Bombay and an industry expert with *12+ years of work experience* in the industry to provide both student and corporate exposure. 

Join us for free session on 30th July, 6 pm.

02/10/2020, 15:27 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Students,

 

Greetings from Institute Innovation and Incubation Cell (IIIC), NIT Durgapur!

 

Institute Innovation and Incubation Centre, NIT Durgapur is glad to announce the very first edition of INNOVATION CONTEST 2020, to identify the creative minds of our institute and cultivate a culture of innovation and entrepreneurship in NIT Durgapur. The contest will be open to all NIT Durgapur students and is intended to provide students with a 360-degree cycle of learning and understanding the process of innovation and start-up. It is designed in a way that each student will traverse a path from problem identification and ideation to building a business model and finally entering the phase of enterprise development in a time period of one year.

 

 AWARD

 

1.      Top 3 best innovative ideas will be awarded by our Director sir with certificate and trophy. [ Best innovative idea trophy, 2020 of our institute]

 

2.      Students of top 25 ideas will be given in-house and external training, incubation support and industry back up to make prototype and commercialize.

 

TIMELINE OF EVENTS:

 

1. Proposal Round: Students can register themselves and submit a brief description of their project ideas through the following link:

 

REGISTRATION LINK: http://bit.ly/30xdgCz

 

LastDate of Submission: 20th October 2020

 

2. Presentation and Shortlisting of Ideas For Prototype Formation: Once the ideas are submitted, shortlisted students will be called for a detailed presentation of the ideas followed by an interview in front of a panel of professors of the IIIC. The panel will evaluate the ideas and the top three ideas will be declared as the winner of the Innovation Contest, 2020 by IIIC, NIT Durgapur. Further, the top few ideas from this round will be eligible to receive incubation support from IIIC, NIT Durgapur to build viable prototype. The number of students eligible for this will depend on the discretion of the panel.

 

3. Prototype Formation: The IIIC, NIT Durgapur team will be in constant touch with the selected students and provide every possible assistance to them to build a viable prototype and further, commercialize their product. The students will receive infrastructure and space, funding, access to business support services and mentorship from the institute so that the idea is transformed into a successful product.

 

EVALUATION CRITERIA:  

 

The ideas will be judged and shortlisted on the following criteria:

 

1. Whether the identified problem really exists in Society/Market/ Industry?

2. How specifically the proposed solution resolves the identified problem?

3. Given the resources available, how realistic is the student’s approach to achieve the solution in a time bound manner?

4. Level of acceptance of Solution/Features among target group

5. Potential of solution to Become profitable or financially viable

 

WHY PARTICIPATE?

 

1. Participate and stand a chance to receive incubation services from the institute to give shape to your dream project.

2. Get a chance to interact with industry experts and get year-round personal mentorship.

3. Gain valuable insights into the process of building a successful startup.

4. Certificate of recognition for the shortlisted students and Participation certificate for every student.  

 

Bill Gates. Mark Zuckerberg. Larry Page. Sergey Brin. They share more than a few enviable accomplishments. They’re billionaires, they made their fortunes in tech and they started their businesses while they were still ‘students’. Undoubtedly, student life is one of the best times to venture into the world of innovation and entrepreneurship. Innovation Contest 2020 is, therefore, the right platform for the students of NIT Durgapur to give shape to their entrepreneurial dreams, with the institute supporting them through all the stages.

 

IIIC urges every student of NIT Durgapur, across all the departments and years, to come forward with their ideas and make the most of the wonderful opportunity in front of them. All the best!

 

Best regards,

 

 

অনুপম বসু
Anupam Basu  Ph.D  FNAE

Director 

National Institute of Technology, Durgapur

&
Professor (on-lien)
Dept. of Computer Science & Engineering (CSE)
IIT Kharagpur 721302
04/10/2020, 11:36 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Prof. Roy,

As discussed, sharing the details of the proposed program. It would be great if the college administration can help us with this initiative.

We at workat.tech are providing our 'Learn to Code in C/C++' program for free exclusively to students of NIT Durgapur.

Prerequisite: Student from any department with a willingness to learn :)

The courses in this program are beginner-friendly and people from all departments are encouraged to use this opportunity to learn to code. After the end of the program, you'll be able to start your coding journey in C and C++ on any online programming platform.

This is a self-paced learn-by-doing program so you will be writing a lot of code while doing the course to build expertise.

You will get access to the courses for 4 months starting from 1st October 2020. You can easily complete both the courses and all the practice problems in a month if you give avg. 2-3 hours per day. You can complete it based on your convenience.

Steps to register:
- Fill this form. Make sure to add your college email address.
- Sign up on workat.tech with your college email address.

Topics to be covered:
- Writing your first code in C [printf]
- Doing arithmetic operations through code [+, -, *, /, %]
- Learning how to store data [variables & data types]
- Learning how to dynamically take input [scanf]
- Learning about other types of operators [Relational, Logical, and Assignment Operators]
- Implementing conditional logic [if-else and switch]
- Doing repeated tasks through loops [for and while loops]
- Making your code clean and reusable [Functions]
- Understanding how all of this works internally [Bits & Bytes, Memory & Pointers, Compilation & Execution]
- Storing sequence of data [Arrays, String]
- Transitioning to C++ from C

Form Link: http://bit.ly/learn-to-code-nitd

Regards,
Gaurav Chandak,
Co-Founder, workat.tech,
NIT Durgapur Alumnus, IT 2016

12/10/2020, 11:14 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Students of VII Sem CE batch,

As you are aware, the scheduled period for arranging Continuous Assessment I for CEE721 is going to be from 13th - 17th Oct. Please submit an assignment for this phase of continuous assessment as per the following:

Description of the Assignment: (Total Marks : 15)

A. (Marks: 10)
 Provide the information regarding the air pollution standards to be followed as per recommendations of:
(i) US EPA / WHO
(ii) CPCB, India.

B. (Marks: 05)
 Then suggest the methodology to be followed by you to ---
(a) prepare a report on air pollution inventory in your locality, &
(b) describe the steps you will follow in collection of air samples for determination of the values of ambient air quality parameters in your locality.

Instructions for preparation & submission of assignment report (to be followed strictly) :

1. Open a blank word document & write your full name & complete roll number on the first page.

2. Give a heading of ASSIGNMENT-1 ON AIR POLLUTION on the first page itself.

3. Start inserting data collected by you regarding items (i) & (ii) mentioned under A above from page 2 onwards.

4. Write answers to items (a) & (b) under B above in your own words only. Any evidence of mutual sharing of reports for Item B will lead to deduction of marks for all reports involved in the same.

5. Once you are finished with the above, convert your assignment report to a pdf file. Please watch that the file size does not exceed the standard maximum permissible size of an email attachment.

6. Please save the pdf with the filename containing your respective roll no. in the following style as :  CEE721_Assignment1_ 17CE8004.pdf   <-----  sample for Roll No. 8004. 

8. Send the attachment to my office email already being used to communicate with you. In the subject line of the mail please write the used filename once again as:
     CEE721_Assignment1_ 17CE8004   <-----  sample for Roll No. 8004. Try to send the assignment report preferably from your official email id of NITD.

9. The last date of submission of the assignment is 15.10.2020. No assignment will be accepted after that.

Best wishes,

S. Bhattacharyya,
Subject teacher, CEE721.

13/10/2020, 19:49 - Manisha @ NIT Dgp Civil: 🏷️value proposition: Quality of the value
🏷️Successful companies bare strongly customer focused
🏷️Marketing Deals with customers
📧Marketing Process👉👉👉👉👉
1)🙀Understand Customer Needs
2)💰Develop a market Strategy
3)💻Develop an integrated marketing program :
      📈  Four Ps of Marketing-- Product, Price, Place and Promotion
4) 😘Build Customer relationship
5) 🛑Capturing Value from customers
 Consumer Buying Behaviour ---
The behaviour that consumers display in searching for, purchasing,using, evaluating and disposing of products and services that they expect will satisfy their needs( Schiffman, Kanuk and Kumar)

🛑Factors affecting Consumer Buying       📈Behaviour-
1) Cultural Factors( customs,values,norms and social behaviour that exists in a particular society )
2)  Social Factors ( Society more or less permanent division whose members share similar values interests and behaviours     )
@ upper class
@ middle class 
@ Lower class
3) Personal Factors
4) Psychological Factors ---
 personality, motivation, perception, learning

Consumer Buying Process👉👉👉👉
1) Need Recognition
2) Information Search
3) Evaluation of alternatives
4) Purchase Decision
5) Post purchase evaluation

24/11/2020, 12:11 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Students of VII Sem CE batch,

Please note the following carefully:

Instructions for submission of answer document for the test for Continuous Assessment 2 to be held on 26.11.2020 from 3:00p.m. (to be followed strictly) :

1. Use plain white sheets of paper for writing the answers in your own handwriting.

2. Please write your name, roll no. & page no. on top of all of such sheets used by you. Keep these sheets ready before the start of the test. 

3. The question will be sent to you by mail, approximately 10 min. before the scheduled start of the examination.

4. Write answers to all questions.as there will be no alternatives.

5. Write answers in your own words only. Any evidence of mutual sharing of answers will lead to deduction of marks for all answer sheets involved in the same.

6. The scheduled time of the end of the test is 4:30p.m. (i.e. the duration of the test is 90min.).

7. Use the next 30 min. to prepare the answer document for submission by email as per the following steps. 

8. Once you have finished writing the answers, take photographs of all pages of the answer sheet clearly & sequentially.

9. Now, open a blank word document & write your full name & complete roll number on the first page. Give a heading of Continuous Assessment 2 on the first page itself.

10. Paste the photographs of your answer sheets on the subsequent pages of the word document. Paste the photograph of only one page of answer sheet on each page of the word document.

11. Cover the full extent of each page of the word document so that your answers are fully viewable.

12. Now convert the complete word file with all answers pasted in it to a pdf file.  Please watch that the file size does not exceed the standard maximum permissible size of an email attachment.

13. Please save the pdf with the filename containing your respective roll no. in the following style as :  17CE8004_CEE721_CA2.pdf   <-----  sample for Roll No. 17CE8004.  

14.  Send the attachment at the earliest to my office email already being used to communicate with you.

15. The last time of receiving the answer document is 5:00 p.m. on 26.11.2020. No answer document will be accepted after that.


Best wishes,

S. Bhattacharyya,
Subject teacher, CEE721.

14/12/2020, 00:10 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Unlike traditional closed book exams where students are required to rely solely on their recall of exam topics, open book exams allow students to consult reference materials (notes, textbook, etc.) in the course of completing the exam. Just because an exam is open book doesn't mean it will be easier, or any less challenging, than a closed book exam. In fact, the opposite is often true. While closed book exams place emphasis on memorization and recall, open book exams place focus on higher level learning and typically require students to evaluate, analyze, or synthesize information, rather than simply remember it.

27/12/2020, 11:34 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Students of VII Sem CE batch,

As you are aware (and further confirmed from your CR) the end semester examination for CEE721 is going to be held as per the following :

Scheduled date : 29.12.2020 (Tuesday)

Reporting time : Get connected to the Google meet link used by us for the online class of CEE721 positively within 9:05a.m. and keep your video in on position to show yourself on the screen for the rest of the duration of the test till online submission of your answer documents.

Time : 9:15a.m. - 11.45a.m.

Last time of acceptance of answer scripts by email by me : 12:15p.m.

Course content for the test: As per the text files CEE721_7.pdf - CEE721_23.pdf (i.e. upto the end of the interaction on CEE721) 

[While accessing the files from the concerned folder in Google Drive, use your NITD email id ONLY. If you still face any problem, please contact your CR Sourav Das for sharing the same files from his own archive.]

Instructions for submission of answer document for the test for end semester to be held on 29.12.2020 from 9:15a.m. (in line with the instructions sent for CA2 & to be followed strictly) :

1. Use plain white sheets of paper for writing the answers in your own handwriting.

2. Please write your name, roll no. & page no. on top of all of such sheets used by you. Keep these sheets ready before the start of the test. 

3. The question will be sent to you by mail, approximately 10 min. before the scheduled start of the examination.

4. Write answers to all questions.as per the instructions: the pattern of the question may be taken as follows:

(a) Short answer type theory based questions (no alternatives) : 30nos. x 1mark each = 30 marks.
(b) Numerical based (5 nos. questions to be selected out of 7) : 5nos. x 6marks each =  30 marks.
                                                                                                                             TOTAL :  60 marks 

5. Write answers in your own words only. Any evidence of mutual sharing of answers will lead to deduction of marks for all answer sheets involved in the same.

6. The scheduled time of the end of the test is 11:45a.m. (i.e. the duration of the test is 2 & 1/2 hrs.).

7. Use the next 30 min. to prepare the answer document for submission by email as per the following steps. 

8. Once you have finished writing the answers, take photographs of all pages of the answer sheet clearly & sequentially.

9. Now, open a blank word document & write your full name & complete roll number on the first page. Give a heading of End Semester Examination (VII), 2020-21 on the first page itself.

10. Paste the photographs of your answer sheets on the subsequent pages of the word document. Paste the photograph of only one page of answer sheet on each page of the word document.

11. Cover the full extent of each page of the word document so that your answers are fully viewable.

12. Now convert the complete word file with all answers pasted in it to a pdf file.  Please watch that the file size does not exceed the standard maximum permissible size of an email attachment.

13. Please save the pdf with the filename containing your respective roll no. in the following style as :  17CE8004_CEE721_EndSem.pdf   <-----  sample for Roll No. 17CE8004.  

14.  Send the attachment at the earliest to my office email already being used to communicate with you.

15. The last time of receiving the answer document is 12:15 p.m. on 29.12.2020. No answer document will be accepted after that.

16. Preserve all the original answer document with you for any reference in future, if necessary.

Best wishes,

S. Bhattacharyya,
Subject teacher, CEE721

03/03/2021, 00:01 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Sir/Ma’am,


As you are aware that the TEQIP-III project is going to end on 31st March 2021, to know the impacts of the equity interventions implemented by the institutes the World bank has planned for conducting a series of surveys. The EAP (Equity Action Plan) has been instrumental in guiding institutes in thinking approaches to improve students' learning and performance, promoting equity among students, and enhancing faculty productivity and motivation to teach and produce research. All these interventions have resulted in tangible outcomes; enhanced employability skills and better placements, including students from disadvantaged groups. 



The objective of this survey is to get direct feedback from one of the important stakeholders i.e., students. The responses from the students will be used to inform the universities/ institutions to better prepare for such activities and support students adequately.



You are requested to circulate the google form to all your students and request them to submit the responses before 10th March 2021. The form will take only 2 minutes to fill. EAP coordinator of the institutions/ATUs are requested to forward one copy of the email that will be send to the students to NPIU at npiu-mhrd@gov.in



The link of the google form is:



https://forms.gle/om7LcA2sxXGUJwgR6

14/03/2021, 14:21 - Sourav @ NIT Dgp | Civil: Dear Students,

Transportation is the movement of people or goods from one place to another by means of a vehicle, aircraft, or ship. Several studies have been conducted regarding how people travel and the transportation modes utilised by them over time. These studies have largely contributed to the development and optimization of transportation modes, thus improving security, punctuality, conform and efficiency for travellers. 

This survey is a part of a study where we are trying to explore how University students travel, students being one of the most important stakeholders of the nation. The direct responses of the students we get through this survey will be used for the development of transportation facilities for them. Thus, we are tirelessly working for the welfare of the student community. We ask of you students, your humble contribution to make this study successful and help make the world a little better place to live in.

You are requested to circulate the form amongst all the students of your university to help gain a greater response.

All the CRs (Class Representatives) and TPRs of the various sections and departments, irrespective of the course you are enrolled in, are hereby requested to circulate this form amongst the respective students and insist them to fill up the form as soon as possible. 

This form will hardly take 5-6 minutes to fill up. We humbly request your sincere contribution.

The link for the Google Form survey is given below

*https://forms.gle/rbAcWRNZ7M2pprT47*

26/05/2021, 14:16 - Madhav Mishra @ NIT Dgp | Civil: कॉलेज के वो दिन, लौट के ना आएंगे।
फिर से जैसे दोस्त, ना कभी मिल पाएंगे।

कैंटीन कि वह चाय, क्लास के लिए
हम कभी समय पर ना पहुँच पाए।

यारो, चाहे कितने दूर चले जाओ,
पर साथ रहेंगे यादों के साये।

एक साथ कैंटीन में बैठक,
लोगों को उतारना।

ग़लती सबकी होती थी पर,
किसी एक पर बिल फाड़ना।

जन्मदिन के केक का,
जो होता था बुरा हाल।

कॉलेज में सब ग़रीब होते थे,
पैसों का रहता था काल।


 
बेचारे हॉस्टल वालों के,
अलग होते थे रोने।

ना अच्छा खाना और,
कपड़े भी थे धोने।

हर हँसी और ग़म में,
हम एक दूजे के साथ खड़े थे।

हर मुसीबत में यह कदम,
साथ में आगे बढ़े थे।

एक छोटा सा परिवार,
बन गया था हमारा।

दोस्त ही होते थे,
एक दूजे का सहारा।

कॉलेज के वो दिन,
लौट के ना आएंगे।

फिर से वैसे दोस्त,
ना कभी मिल पाएंगे।।

26/05/2021, 19:26 - Navya @ NIT Dgp | Civil: From "how we will survive in this department " to "it went very fast" is a beautiful journey filled with lots of fun , entertainment and tears and tensions too. But  i can't digest it is going to end today .It started with the fear of supply in adhikari sir subject, long class hours, coming to class @8:30am right from the bed with sleepy face, contacting seniors to know profs behaviour and listening to their Bitter experiences, playing games in the last bench in sb sir's class, laughing to dwivedi sir meaningless jokes ,bunking coolest p ray sir class  ,the long-standing labs,the 5th sem is like hell, The tension of facing profs in viva and being ragged by profs, nightouts to complete bundle of assignments which never end ,and the drawing lab where we depend much on classmates than profs, entering to sb sir's class in the last minute ,akb sir solving problem sitting along with us and no one get solution he asked for, nearly 15 members sitting on the same bench to escape from sitting in the first bench in dsr sir's class, hating dsr sir's for the torcher in sessionals and for lengthy assignments nearly 12 assignments for 4 marks,sitting sk sir who look cool in 3rd sem became strict in structural class,pretending like seriously listening in classes and writing notes in kb and sp class ,fun in surveying lab and the boring estimation session, standing at aks sir door to compain about long extra class hours, pretending like we are listening to proy sir in concrete lab , laughing out loudest to the jokes of Mukhopadhyay sir , our ss sir who won't come to class without a book in his hand, attempting lengty design papers, 3hrs soil class on Friday with 15 minutes break where we all were in nescafe and zhoops ,sheru who became our teacher in concrete lab, how can We forget our mighty Raju class showing ppt and reading the same and telling something which no one get,hating the department now and then for not giving us free time for preparing gate and other competitive exams ,the departmental trip where we found the coolest side of profs, and sending assignments done by classmates changing name and roll number thanks to those classmates, evng classes by ad which most of us didn't listen at all,fear of getting supply in sediment transport ended with getting 10 almost everyone in the class. online computational lab where we screenshared the file we got from frnds, scary mails from Project guide, waiting for the hectic Project to end soon ,last 2 days we were busy in entertaining profs,.
atlast the uneasy feeling I got when profs call me with my surname and yesterday's emotional mail by ad sir...cheers to all of us .All these became sweet and beautiful memories now ..yeah these all are going to end today .but I used to all these and gonna miss them badly ..I wish all my dear classmates a successful life with your loved ones. Best of luck ❤️ ~ Navya

08/07/2021, 13:14 - Abishek @ NIT Dgp | Civil: https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/2581835198/
13/07/2021, 10:09 - Abishek @ NIT Dgp | Civil: BARC Training Schools - Online Applications are Invited from Science Post Graduates and Engineering Graduates to Apply for Scientific Officers (Group-A Post of Government of India) through its Academic Programs OCES/DGFS-2021, Department of Atomic Energy (DAE), Government of India

BARC Training Schools Invite Engineering Graduates and Science Post Graduates - 2021:
• Who would relish challenges in frontier areas of Science and Technology
• Who would like to be part of an expanding program of Nuclear Reactors, Accelerators and Fuel Cycle Technologies
• Who would enjoy pursuing innovative research in Engineering, Physics, Chemistry, Biosciences or Geology

TRAINING SCHEMES AND EMPLOYMENT DESCRIPTION
1. One-Year Orientation Course for Engineering Graduates and Science Postgraduates for the year 2021-2022 (OCES-2021):

OCES-2021 will be conducted at the BARC Training Schools. Table-1 lists Eligible Disciplines. Table-2 lists the Eligible Disciplines and orientation of the Training Program at each of the Training Schools. A Trainee Scientific Officer (TSO), who scores a minimum of 50% aggregate marks on completion of the Training Program, is declared to have completed the course successfully. Successful TSOs will be posted as Scientific Officers in one of the following DAE units:

a) Bhabha Atomic Research Centre (BARC), Mumbai
b) Indira Gandhi Centre for Atomic Research (IGCAR), Kalpakkam
c) Raja Ramanna Centre for Advanced Technology (RRCAT), Indore
d) Variable Energy Cyclotron Centre (VECC), Kolkata
e) Heavy Water Board (HWB), Mumbai
f) Nuclear Fuel Complex (NFC), Hyderabad
g) Board of Radiation and Isotope Technology (BRIT), Mumbai
h) Nuclear Power Corporation of India Ltd (NPCIL), Mumbai
i) Bharatiya Nabhikiya Vidyut Nigam Ltd (BHAVINI), Kalpakkam
j) Atomic Minerals Directorate for Exploration & Research (AMD), Hyderabad
k) Uranium Corporation of India Ltd (UCIL), Jaduguda
l) Directorate of Construction, Services and Estate Management (DCS&EM), Mumbai

Allocation of a successful OCES TSO to a DAE unit is carried out based on the needs of DAE’s programs and the TSO’s performance in the OCES program. DAE reserves the right to place TSOs in any of its other units also or the Atomic Energy Regulatory Board (AERB).

Performance above a specified threshold in course work at the Training School will entitle TSOs to a Post-Graduate Diploma or could earn them credits towards M.Tech./M.Phil./Ph.D. programs of Homi Bhabha National Institute (HBNI), a deemed to be University.

Two-Year DAE Graduate Fellowship Scheme for Engineering Graduates and Physics Postgraduates for the years 2021-2023 (DGFS-2021):

Under this scheme, Engineering Graduates and Physics Postgraduates who have excelled in the Selection Interviews for the BARC Training Schools’ program and who have independently secured admission for M.Tech./M.Chem. Engg. in select Institutes and specializations as listed in Table-3, are paid stipend and tuition fee to pursue a M.Tech./M.Chem.Engg. degree while retaining their employment in DAE. After successful completion of one-year course work at the Institute, Fellows undertake project work, which is assigned by DAE and supervised jointly by a DAE guide and an Institute guide. On successful completion of M.Tech./M.Chem.Engg., they are posted as Scientific Officers in DAE. On joining, they are required to first undertake a four-month Orientation Course for DGFS Fellows (OCDF) at the BARC Training School, Mumbai.

The DGFS Fellows are enrolled and posted in one of the following units of DAE:
a) BARC, Mumbai, b) IGCAR, Kalpakkam.
Allocation of a DGFS Fellow to a DAE unit is done at the beginning of the M.Tech./M.Chem. Engg. program.

* Selected candidates are required to execute an agreement and a personal Indemnity. Bond to serve DAE for at least three years after completion of Training. Indemnity Bond is for Rs.6,78,000 for OCES TSOs and Rs. 13,58,000 for DGFS Fellows#. No third party surety is required.

* The Bond Amount for DGFS Fellows pursuing M.Tech./M.Chem. Engg. at certain DGFS Institutes may be different, depending on the tuition fee at the concerned Institute.

OCES-2021:
One Year Orientation Course for Engineering Graduates & Science Postgraduates starting in December, 2021 will be conducted at BARC Training Schools situated at: BARC, Mumbai; IGCAR, Kalpakkam; NFC, Hyderabad; RRCAT, Indore; AMD, Hyderabad.

DGFS-2021:
Two Year DAE Graduate Fellowship Scheme for Engineering Graduates and Physics Postgraduates for joining M.Tech. / M.Chem. Engg. in select specializations starting in July 2021 at : Indian Institute of Technology (IIT)–Bombay, Delhi, Guwahati, Kanpur, Kharagpur, Madras, Roorkee and BHU-Varanasi; National Institute of Technology (NIT) - Rourkela; Institute of Chemical Technology (ICT) – Mumbai.

During Training:
(i) Stipend and Allowances: OCES TSOs and DGFS Fellows are paid  a stipend of Rs. 55,000 per month during the period of their Training. Additionally, they are paid a one-time book allowance of Rs. 18,000.

(ii) DGFS Fellows are reimbursed the tuition fee for M.Tech. / M.Chem. Engg.and are additionally paid a one-time Contingency Grant of Rs. 25,000 to meet M.Tech. / M.Chem. Engg. project related expenses.(iii) Boarding and Lodging in DAE or DGFS Institute Hostel respectively, during Training, is mandatory.

Important Dates:
- Last date for Registration for Online Application: 7 August 2021
- Online Examination Slot Booking: 20-25 August 2021
- Online Examination : 5-12 September 2021
- Display of List of candidates short-listed for Interview on Online Application Portal: 21 September 2021
- Selection Interviews: 4-29 October 2021
- Declaration of List of Applicants Selected for DGFS-2021 on Online Application Portal: 30 November 2021

Online Portal:
http://www.barconlineexam.in/

Advertisement:
http://www.barconlineexam.in/science/documents/Advertisement-2021.pdf

Website Links:
http://www.barconlineexam.in/science/index.html
